				<p>Owh yes, thats a good point. Thanks. Besides the effect of centrifugal force,  do you think vibrations will affect the IMU's readings? I mean, will the IMU still gives out the same readings at the same orientation before and after experiencing vibrations? Of course the imu is calibrated before hand.</p>
			</div>
			<div id = "comment-13171" class = "comment">
				<p>During the vibration-phase the accelerometer might produce non sense. Depends on the amplitude of the vibration. Basically vibrations do not alter the IMU sensor if they are under a certain threshold. You can find this value in datasheets usually. If you hit the sensor with a force which is exceeding the acceleration limit, then the sensor's measurement can be changed. But we are talking about the range of 100,000 m/s  for MEMS.</p>
